refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayPDOStatement::getColumnMeta intcolumn
&warn.experimental.func;
Retrieves the metadata for a 0-indexed column in a result set as an associative array.
Not all PDO drivers support PDOStatement::getColumnMeta.

&reftitle.parameters;




   column



      The 0-indexed column in the result set.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Retrieving column metadata


     The following example shows the results of retrieving the metadata for a
     single column generated by a function (COUNT) in a PDO_SQLITE driver.



<?php
$select = $DB->query('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fruit');
$meta = $select->getColumnMeta(0);
var_dump($meta);
?>


    &example.outputs;


array(6) {
  ["native_type"]=>
  string(7) "integer"
  ["flags"]=>
  array(0) {
  }
  ["name"]=>
  string(8) "COUNT(*)"
  ["len"]=>
  int(-1)
  ["precision"]=>
  int(0)
  ["pdo_type"]=>
  int(2)
}
